history.content: I'll let Anant comment on final scheduling options for EE16A, but assuming you were planning to take three technical courses and that the Physics 7B final isn't the same day, taking CS61A, EE16A, and Physics 7B is a perfectly reasonable option.  Or, you could take just CS61A and EE6A and fill in the rest of your schedule with non-technical courses; the vast majority of upper-div. EECS courses are gated by the CS61/EE16 series (not by math/physics), so if you choose this option you'd still be in great shape in terms of getting yourself ready for the rest of the program.

I have switched into EE16A but realized that its final is in the slot right before my Math 53 (lecture 2) final. The Math 54 class and section 1 of Math 53 class are both full. I could take Physics 7B instead of EE16A, but from all the discussion about taking EE16A, I think I would rather take EE16A first semester. So is there anything else I can do to avoid 2 finals on the same day?
history.subject: EE16A and Math 53 final on the same day
